@node readme "Author's words."

	Author's words
	--------------

	  Well, you may  ask what the heck is  this what you are  holding
	right now. A package of small shell tools. What are they for? Who
	needs them anyway? Go ahead, read on.

	  I have  written these  programs for a long time.  Always when I
	didn't  know where  to get a  program to do  someting specific, I
	wrote one  myself. Now,  when I have done  quite a bunch of these
	"little helpers"  I thought that  someone else  would like to use
	them too. That's when  I started to write  this text that I could
	upload this package to Aminet.

	  As you may already guess,  these programs  are meant to be used
	from AmigaShell only. If you have newer KickStart than 1.3, there
	is no use in putting these programs into WBStarup -drawer. If you
	want to launch  them upon booting,  you have to use  User-Startup
	file to do that. Remember  also to use Run command since my tools
	won't detach themselves.

	  What else? You are free to  use these programs, but if you like
	them and keep using them frequently, then drop me a mail. I would
	like to hear your  comments about the programs, too.  Also if you
	are a programmer yourself then take a look at the Sources drawer.
	I've included  sources of some  programs there.  I wasn't able to
	include them all,  because my HD  crashed a  while ago and I lost
	them. Yes, it's too bad, I'm not able to make bugfixes  the those
	programs, but they are working  so who actually cares. :) Sources
	are also free to use, but if you make modifications to them, then
	drop me a mail, too.  I want to hear  possible improvement ideas.
	My email addy is quaid@kempele.fi.

	  BTW: All programs are written in assembly language.

@endnode

@node sources "Developer information"

	@{b}Developer information.@{ub}
	----------------------

	  As you  might have seen,  some of the sources for  the programs
	are  also  available.  They are  written using  SNMA v2.54  (Samu
	Nuojua's  Macro  Assembler).  It's  a  macro  assembler  that  is
	familiar with  all mc680x0  processors. If you  like to use macro
	assembler instead  of monitor and you don't  have SNMA yet,  then
	download it right now from AmiNet. dev/asm/snma???.lha

	  Enough of commercial break.  Well, I think that the sources are
	clean enough to compile  again with any  other assembler,  but it
	might be  possible that  you have to  do some  modifications  for
	them.

	  I've  included those  sources because I  know I'm not  the best
	programmer in the world and that's why there exists more talented
	people to fix my  errors. I was  not able  to include the sources
	for all  programs, because  I had a HD  crash lately  and part of
	package was  lost. The programs  which sources I lost contain few
	bugs,  but because  the sources  do not exist  anymore, they  are
	impossible to fix.

	  Sources are totally yours to use but with one condition. If you
	modify the program in a way that it  might help others, too, then
	you  mustn't be hesitating to  inform me about your changes.  I'd
	like to add your cool features for  my versions. And  because the
	sources  are written  by me and  because I've  released  them for
	public domain,  your sources are public  domain, too.  That means
	that  if someone would  like  to see  the sources  that you  have
	modified, you have no right to  refuse. You don't need to  upload
	them to anywhere, they just need to be available if someone wants
	them.

@endnode

